oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: John Jared unhooking 13" rainbow trout caught in Crumpton Creek near Tullahoma, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of John Jared unhooking a 13" rainbow trout he caught in Crumpton's Creek near Tullahoma, Tenn. He is sitting on the river bank on some rocks near the water's edge. His fishing rod is still attached to the trout. Jared is wearing a cap, fishing vest, pants and is smoking a pipe. There is a man, trees and water in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
